<section id="shell_usage">
	<title>Shell Management Commands</title>
	<section id="shell_connect_command">
		<title>Connect Shell to Managed Instance</title>
			<variablelist>
				<title><command>connect</command> command</title>
				<varlistentry>
					<term>Name</term>
					<listitem><para>connect</para></listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term>SYNOPSIS</term>
					<listitem><para>connect &lt;host-ip&gt; &lt;host-port&gt;</para></listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term>DESCRIPTION</term>
					<listitem><para>This command is used to connect the Shell to a managed instance. The parameters
        &lt;host-ip&gt; and &lt;host-port&gt; are optional. If you do not specify them, the shell will
        attempt connecting to 127.0.0.1:3435.</para></listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term>PARAMETERS</term>
					<listitem><para>
					  Optional Parameters
<itemizedlist>
<listitem><para>
        &lt;host-ip&gt;               -       The host IP address of the system the Shell will
                                        connect to.</para></listitem>
<listitem><para>
        &lt;host-port&gt;             -       The host port of the managed instance, which the
                                        Shell will bind to.</para></listitem>
</itemizedlist>
					</para></listitem>
				</varlistentry>
				<varlistentry>
					<term>EXAMPLES</term>
					<listitem><para>connect 10.65.208.215 3435</para>
	<para>The above command will connect the Shell to the IP address 10.65.208.215 and
        port 3435.</para></listitem>
				</varlistentry>
		<!--		<varlistentry>
